Integrated UMAP from zebrafish telencephalon including 6 dpf, 15 dpf, and adult samples.

#create dpf15 objects
B1 <- Read10X(data.dir = "remappingdpf15/original/B1")
B1 <- CreateSeuratObject(counts = B1, project = "15dpf_b1", min.features = 200)
B2 <- Read10X(data.dir = "remappingdpf15/original/B2")
B2 <- CreateSeuratObject(counts = B2, project = "15dpf_b2", min.features = 200)
B3 <- Read10X(data.dir = "remappingdpf15/original/B3")
B3 <- CreateSeuratObject(counts = B3, project = "15dpf_b3", min.features = 200)
B4 <- Read10X(data.dir = "remappingdpf15/original/B4")
B4 <- CreateSeuratObject(counts = B4, project = "15dpf_b4", min.features = 200)

#merge 15dpf objects
dpf15.merged <- merge(B1, y = c(B2, B3, B4), add.cell.ids = c("15dpf_b1", "15dpf_b2", "15dpf_b3", "15dpf_b4"), project = "dpf15")

#add "age" column with 15dpf

allages.merged$age <- as.factor(allages.merged$age)

allages.merged <- SetIdent(allages.merged, value = "age")

2 Integrated analysis

2.1 Log normalize

LogNormalize normalizes the feature expression measurements for each cell by the total expression, multiplies this by a scale factor (10,000 by default), and log-transforms the result.

#split by age
allages.list <- SplitObject(allages.merged, split.by = "batch")

#log normalize each object in allsampleslist
allages.list <- lapply(X = allages.list, FUN = function(x) {
    x <- NormalizeData(x, normalization.method = "LogNormalize", scale.factor = 10000)
})

2.2 Feature selection

#feature selection using Seurat
allages.list <- lapply(X = allages.list, FUN = function(x) {
    x <- FindVariableFeatures(x, selection.method = "vst", nfeatures = 2000)
})

#find variable features (SP)
require(MASS)
new.meanCVfit <- function(count.data, diffCV.cutoff=3, mean.min=.005, mean.max=1000, main.use="", do.plot=T) {
  
  # Format for the plot
  if (do.plot) par(mfrow=c(1,3), oma=c(0,0,2,0))
  
  # Calculate empirical mean, var and CV
  mean_emp <- apply(count.data, 1, mean)
  var_emp <- apply(count.data, 1, var)
  cv_emp <- sqrt(var_emp) / mean_emp
  
  # Fit gamma distribution to 'size factors' to build negative binomial
  a <- colSums(count.data)
  size_factor <- a/mean(a)
  fit <- fitdistr(size_factor, "Gamma")
  if (do.plot) {
    print(fit)
    hist(size_factor, 50, probability=TRUE, xlab="UMIs per cell / mean UMIs per cell", main=paste0("Size Factors & Gamma Fit (a=", round(fit$estimate[1], 2), ")"))
    curve(dgamma(x, shape=fit$estimate[1], rate=fit$estimate[2]),from=0, to=quantile(size_factor, 0.999), add=TRUE, col="red")
  }
  
  # Create null negative binomial distribution
  #   Gamma distributions of individual genes are just scaled versions. If X ~ Gamma(a,b)
  #   then cX ~ Gamma(a, b/c)
  a_i <- rep(fit$estimate[1], length(mean_emp))
  names(a_i) <- names(mean_emp)
  b_i <- fit$estimate[2] / mean_emp
  names(b_i) <- names(mean_emp)
  mean_NB <- a_i / b_i
  var_NB <- a_i*(1+b_i) / (b_i^2)
  cv_NB <- sqrt(var_NB)/mean_NB
  
  # Calculate difference in genes' CV and null CV
  diffCV = log(cv_emp) - log(cv_NB)
  if (do.plot) {
    hist(diffCV, 150, xlab="log(CVgene / CVnull)", main="Diff CV")
    abline(v=diffCV.cutoff, lty=2, col='red')
  }
  pass.cutoff <- names(diffCV)[which(diffCV > diffCV.cutoff & (mean_emp > mean.min & mean_emp < mean.max))]
  
  # Plot variable gene selection
  if (do.plot) {
    plot(mean_emp,cv_emp,pch=16,cex=0.5,col="black",xlab="Mean Counts",ylab="CV (counts)", log="xy", main = "Selection of Variable Genes")
    curve(sqrt(1/x), add=TRUE, col="red", log="xy", lty=2, lwd=2)
    or = order(mean_NB)
    lines(mean_NB[or], cv_NB[or], col="magenta", lwd=2)
    points(mean_emp[pass.cutoff], cv_emp[pass.cutoff], pch=16, cex=0.5, col='blue')
    title(main.use, outer=T)
  }
  
  # Return list of variable genes
  return(pass.cutoff)
}

#add features from Seurat and SP; set as Variable Features
for(x in 1:length(allages.list)) {
  svg <-VariableFeatures(object = allages.list[[x]])
  SP_genes <- new.meanCVfit(count.data = allages.list[[x]]@assays[["RNA"]]@counts,     diffCV.cutoff=0.4, mean.min=0.005, mean.max=75, main.use="", do.plot=F)
  all.genes <- union(SP_genes, svg)
  VariableFeatures(object = allages.list[[x]]) <- all.genes
}

# select features that are repeatedly variable across datasets for integration
allagesfeatures <- SelectIntegrationFeatures(object.list = allages.list)

2.3 Integration

#find integration anchors 
allages.anchors <- FindIntegrationAnchors(object.list = allages.list, anchor.features = allagesfeatures)

# this command creates an 'integrated' data assay
allages.combined <- IntegrateData(anchorset = allages.anchors)

DefaultAssay(allages.combined) <- "integrated"

allages.combined <- ScaleData(allages.combined)
allages.combined <- RunPCA(allages.combined)
allages.combined <- FindNeighbors(allages.combined, dims = 1:15)
allages.combined <- RunUMAP(allages.combined, dims = 1:15, n.neighbors=5L)
allages.combined <- FindClusters(allages.combined, resolution = 2)

#make csvs with markers
